Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic and @mixed herbs{1%sachet} to the pan and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir through the @tomato puree{60%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%g} and the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{300%ml} for the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, then pop a #lid on the pan (or cover with #foil) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the meat is tender and the sauce has thickened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the mince has ~{15%minutes} of cooking time left, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

When boiling, add the @spaghetti{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

When everything's ready, remove the ragu from the oven and stir through the @butter{20%g}, @olives{30%g} and pasta.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you need to loosen the sauce.

Divide the pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish.

Enjoy!